SUMMARY:Olio Read-in: Kafka's Metamorphosis
DESCRIPTION:"As Gregor Samsa awoke one morning from uneasy dreams he found 
 himself transformed in his bed into a gigantic insect." The enigmatic open
 ing sentence of Kafka's Metamorphosis has been perplexing translators\, in
 spiring illustrators\, and intriguing psychiatrists for over a century. Wh
 at kind of bug is Gregor? Is his transformation a process or a freak accid
 ent? Does his metamorphosis symbolize coming out? Or perils of capitalism?
  Anticipation of fascism? Body dysmorphia? Bad faith? Disability? Marginal
 ity?In this Olio Read-in\, we will be performing a close reading of Part 1
  of Metamorphosis. By focusing on minuscule details — linguistic choices
 \, floor plans\, food crumbs — we will enter Kafka's nightmarish univers
 e that is strikingly similar to our own.Olio Read-ins were started by hist
 orian Jamie Warren:"Rooted in the social revolution of the 1960s\, Read-in
 s have always been essential to the political project of building communit
 ies\, and bolstering progressive change. Read-ins announce: We will not re
 main alone\, afraid\, and cut off from one another. No. We will sit side b
 y side and with the support of each other\, we will read. We will learn. W
 e will enrich our inner world so that we can find the courage to exist out
 side of it."Put simply by one of our Olio members: "Read-Ins are like the 
 book club that I actually want to be a part of. It's so much more fun to e
 ngage with these texts as a group and with a teacher than as a solo activi
 ty." &nbsp\;Teacher: Dina Odnopozova Dina Odnopozova holds a PhD from Yale
  and is a professor at Baruch College\, where her work explores the inters
 ection of literature\, psychology\, and the unconscious. She has led Olios
  on Freud\, Jung\, and the archetypal grammar of fairy tales — the witch
 es\, wolves\, and forbidden doors that map the human subconscious. In this
  Read-in\, she brings that same depth of attention to Kafka.What Is an Oli
 o? Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in lifelong learning. We are a comm
 unity of open-minded people who gather to exchange ideas with new friends 
 and connect over art\, literature\, and philosophy. Check out our full cal
 endar Our $30 membership gives you two events for the price of one!An Olio
  is what we call the social learning events we've been organizing since 20
 15. A blend between a lecture and a house party\, Olios are led by a teach
 er who loves sharing their passions and the room is filled with curious\, 
 open-minded New Yorkers.Our goal is to spark new perspectives\, ignite cur
 iosity\, and enjoy ourselves socially—an alternative to typical nightlif
 e options.Disclaimer: By purchasing a ticket\, you agree to have your phot
 o/video used for social media/marketing materials. If you prefer to not ha
 ve your photo taken\, feel free to send us a note. Photo by Zhi-Da Zhong\n
 \nTickets & info: https://www.viewcy.com/event/olio_readin_kafkas
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/olio_readin_kafkas
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
