SUMMARY:The Tao of Touch: Cultivating Presence and Attunement
DESCRIPTION:The body is always speaking. Learning to touch is\, in part\, l
 earning to listen. We spend so much of our lives in our heads that it's ea
 sy to forget how much wisdom lives in the body. Across cultures\, touch ha
 s long been understood as more than a form of comfort or affection but a w
 ay of communicating care\, restoring balance\, and reminding us that we're
  not meant to move through life alone.In Taoist philosophy\, wellbeing isn
 't something we chase or achieve. It's something we cultivate by learning 
 to live in better relationship with ourselves\, with others\, and with the
  natural rhythms of life. Join Darryl Aiken-Afam for this 3-hour Olio expl
 oring the art of platonic healing touch through the lens of Taoist philoso
 phy.Together we'll explore the foundational ideas of Yin and Yang\, Qi (li
 fe energy)\, and the Five Elements of Chinese Medicine as practical ways o
 f understanding our bodies\, emotions\, and relationships. We'll learn a f
 ew simple Qigong movements to become more grounded and present\, then prac
 tice beginner-friendly self-care and partnered healing touch techniques fr
 om Zen Shiatsu. No experience is needed\, these arts are much more about a
 ttunement and presence than technique.&nbsp\;We'll walk away with practica
 l ways to regulate stress\, feeling more at home in our bodies\, and hopef
 ully experience a different way of relating to yourself and others. this w
 orkshop offers an accessible introduction to practices that have been cult
 ivated for centuries. Our hope is that after this workshop you'll be more 
 able to support your own wellbeing and offer new ways of care to the peopl
 e in your life.Facilitated by Prof. Darryl Aiken-Afam\, MPSDarryl Aiken-Af
 am is a martial artist and practitioner of the Taoist healing and meditati
 on arts\, including Meridian Cleansing Qigong\, Zen Shiatsu\, and Taoist p
 sychology. He is also deeply involved in social justice work. His Contact 
 &amp\; Conversation events help everyday people navigate meaningful conver
 sations about race by weaving together mindfulness\, yoga\, human touch\, 
 and social psychology to create spaces of trust and understanding. Darryl 
 is an ACE Certified Personal Trainer\, holds a Master's Degree in Leadersh
 ip Psychology from Penn State University\, and toured as a keyboardist wit
 h the funk band Cameo in the 1990s.Flow of the day:Intro to Concepts (Yin 
 Yang\, 5 Elements\, Chi Energy\, Taoist Breathing)Qigong Warm Up &nbsp\;Ba
 sic Touch Techniques Solo PracticeTea &amp\; Snack BreakPartner Practice C
 losing ReflectionsWhat Is an Olio?Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in l
 ifelong learning. We are a community of open-minded people who gather to e
 xchange ideas with new friends and connect over art\, literature\, and phi
 losophy.Check out our full calendarOur $30 membership gives you two events
  for the price of oneAn Olio is what we call the social learning events we
 ’ve been organizing since 2015. A blend between a lecture and a house pa
 rty\, Olios are led by a teacher who loves sharing their passions and the 
 room is filled with curious\, open-minded New Yorkers.&nbsp\;Our goal is t
 o spark new perspectives\, ignite curiosity\, and enjoy ourselves socially
 —an alternative to typical nightlife options.Disclaimer: By purchasing a
  ticket\, you agree to have your photo/video used for social media/marketi
 ng materials. If you prefer to not have your photo taken\, feel free to se
 nd us a note.Photo by Zhi-Da Zhong\n\nTickets & info: https://www.viewcy.c
 om/event/the_tao_of_touch_gro
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/the_tao_of_touch_gro
END:VEVENT
