SUMMARY:Intimacy\, Pleasure\, and Joy: A Buddhist take on Relationships
DESCRIPTION:Good relationships are foundational to a meaningful life and th
 ey can be a continuous source of frustration\, disappointment\, and suffer
 ing. Curious about that? Wish you had more skills for getting your needs m
 et?We human beings spend enormous energy seeking connection\, yet intimacy
  can remain mysterious and confusing. We absorb models of relationship fro
 m family\, culture\, and let’s be honest\, a remarkable amount of bad te
 levision. We carry assumptions we’ve never questioned\, habits we inheri
 ted without choosing\, and a baseline loneliness we’ve learned to mistak
 e for normal.Most of what makes relationships hard has less to do with fin
 ding the right person than with cultivating a deeper understanding of what
  we ourselves bring to the exploration. But that can be changed. Relations
 hip building is a learnable skill set. And like most skill sets\, it can b
 e intentionally practiced\, and gradually refined. The quality of our conn
 ections is\, in fact\, surprisingly workable.In this Olio\, we’ll decons
 truct a handful of basic misunderstandings that may be costing you intimac
 y\, pleasure\, and joy. We’ll look honestly at what draws people togethe
 r\, drives them apart\, and what it actually takes to sustain something at
  the deepest level of meaning. The facilitator is a Buddhist Lama. Through
  more than three decades of training she’s found how nearly 3\,000-year 
 old advice offers deep insights into relationship dynamics that are still 
 very much relevant today.If you still feel lonely in a city of 8 million p
 eople\, this might be for you. Come curious. Leave with something useful.O
 ur teacher for the evening: Lama Lekshe (Julia King Tamang) has been prati
 cing Tibetan Buddhism since 1994 in Portland\, Oregon\, Nepal and India. H
 er teachers are Bokar Rinpoche\, Khenpo Lodro Donyo Rinpoche\, and Lama Mi
 chael Conklin. In 2018\, she completed a traditional 3-year meditation ret
 reat in the Shangpa Kagyu tradition. Before retreat\, was a university tea
 cher and a consultant to colleges. Lekshe is the founder of Dekeling.&nbsp
 \;The evening flow:&nbsp\;6:45- Doors open\, grab a drink and get settled&
 nbsp\;7:10-7:30pm - Opening remarks from Lekshe and a guided meditation&nb
 sp\;7:30- Intimacy\, Pleasure\, and Joy: Relationships Olio begins8:15- 8:
 40pm - Audience Q&amp\;A&nbsp\;8:45- Closing meditation?9-10pm - Mingling 
 at the LighthouseWhat Is an Olio?Think Olio is an ongoing experiment in li
 felong learning. We are a community of open-minded people who gather to ex
 change ideas with new friends and connect over art\, literature\, and phil
 osophy.Check out our full calendarOur $30 membership gives you two events 
 for the price of one!&nbsp\;An Olio is what we call the social learning ev
 ents we’ve been organizing since 2015. A blend between a lecture and a h
 ouse party\, Olios are led by a teacher who loves sharing their passions a
 nd the room is filled with curious\, open-minded New Yorkers.&nbsp\;Our go
 al is to spark new perspectives\, ignite curiosity\, and enjoy ourselves s
 ocially offering an alternative to typical nightlife options.Disclaimer: B
 y purchasing a ticket\, you agree to have your photo/video used for social
  media/marketing materials. If you prefer to not have your photo taken\, f
 eel free to send us a note.Photo by Zhi-Da Zhong\n\nTickets & info: https:
 //www.viewcy.com/event/intimacy_pleasure_a
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/intimacy_pleasure_a
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:81ea5734-cca8-4bc3-9eec-b3bd3f83f29e@viewcy.olio
DTSTAMP:20260714T141549Z
DTSTART:20260806T233000Z
DTEND:20260807T013000Z
SUMMARY:Wines of Eastern Europe: Cultural History Through the Senses
DESCRIPTION:An Evening of Culture and the Senses through Wine&nbsp\;Georgia
  — the so-called Cradle of Wine — has treated wine as a sacred substan
 ce for nearly 8\,000 years. Join us for a guided wine tasting social at th
 e Lighthouse\, an evening that travels deep into Eastern Europe and into a
 ncient stories that are still very much alive.&nbsp\;Tonight\, under the g
 uidance of educator Sam Hewiit\, we'll treat wine as a medium. Viewed in t
 his way\, wine carries cultural history directly to the senses. Together\,
  we'll explore the mystic and cultural origins of wines from Georgia\, Slo
 venia and Hungary while talking and sharing about what we discover when we
  pair the delight of these wines with learning for an all encompassing exp
 erience.We'll explore:The birthplace of wineWine as the meeting point betw
 een gods and humansCultural preservation across millenniaHow lessons of in
 dependence and resistance speak to our world todayThe evening opens with a
 n intimate hour of guided tasting in small groups. Then we open it up — 
 a wine-fueled social hour to keep the conversation going.Educator Sam Hewi
 tt will guide us through the history\, myth\, and mysticism surrounding th
 ese remarkable cultures and their connection to wine.&nbsp\; Wine and snac
 ks included in the ticket price. Resources provided: where to buy Georgian
  wine and tasting notes from the evening.\n\nTickets & info: https://www.v
 iewcy.com/event/wines_of_eastern_euro
URL:https://www.viewcy.com/event/wines_of_eastern_euro
END:VEVENT
